      <h1 class='title'>Clinical Trials Directive</h1>
    </div>
    <div class='commons-written-statements-sitting' id='content'>
      
      <cite class='section'>HC Deb 16 July 2003 vol 409 c37WS</cite>
      <a class='permalink column-permalink' id='column_37ws' title='Col. 37WS &mdash; HC Deb 16 July 2003 vol 409 c37WS' name='column_37ws' href='#column_37ws' rel='bookmark'>37WS</a>
      <div class='hentry member_contribution' id='S6CV0409P0-02426'>
        <a name='S6CV0409P0_20030716_CWS_8'>  </a>
        <blockquote cite='http://hansard.millbanksystems.com/people/miss-melanie-johnson' class='contribution_text entry-content'>
          <a class='speech-permalink permalink' href='#S6CV0409P0_20030716_CWS_8' title='Link to this speech by Miss Melanie Johnson' rel='bookmark'>&sect;</a>
          <cite class='member author entry-title'><a href="/people/miss-melanie-johnson" title="Miss Melanie Johnson">The Parliamentary Under-Secretary of State for Health (Miss Melanie Johnson)</a></cite>
          <p class="first-para" id="S6CV0409P0-02426">The draft regulations to transpose the clinical trials directive into domestic law are currently being discussed with stakeholders. The process of developing these regulations fully, at which point they can be laid before Parliament, should therefore be completed some time after Parliament reconvenes in October. I will aim to give a further update at around that time. Member States are required to implement the directive fully by 1 May 2004.</p>
        </blockquote>
      </div>
